74–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  ♂ ‘Wondrous’ or ‘enlightenment’.","2  ♀ ‘Fine jade’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert II de Tartas was born in 1100, in France as the son of Arnaud-Raymond Ier Vicomte de Tartas. He had at least 1 son. He died after 1140, in his hometown."},"et":{"1100–After 1140":"1100–pärast 1140","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1135–1170":"1135–1170","1070–1122":"1070–1122","1135":"1135","Bef 1122":"enne 1122","1100":"1100","1122":"1122","After 1140":"pärast 1140","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1070":"1070","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1100–After 1140":"1100–1140 jälkeen","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1135–1170":"1135–1170","1070–1122":"1070–1122","1135":"1135","Bef 1122":"ennen vuotta 1122","1100":"1100","1122":"1122","After 1140":"1140 jälkeen","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1070":"1070","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"1100–After 1140":"1100–après 1140","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1135–1170":"1135–1170","1070–1122":"1070–1122","1135":"1135","Bef 1122":"avant 1122","1100":"1100","1122":"1122","After 1140":"après 1140","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1070":"1070","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Robert II de Tartas est né en 1100, à France, fils de Arnaud-Raymond Ier Vicomte de Tartas. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé après 1140, dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1100–After 1140":"1100–nach 1140","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1135–1170":"1135–1170","1070–1122":"1070–1122","1135":"1135","Bef 1122":"vor 1122","1100":"1100","1122":"1122","After 1140":"nach 1140","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1070":"1070","France":"Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Robert II de Tartas wurde 1100 in Frankreich, als Sohn von Arnaud-Raymond Ier Vicomt